HEADWORD: Decilitre
<hw>Dec"i*li`tre</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧cilitre</ets>; pref.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧ci-</ets> tenth (L. <ets>decimus</ets>) +
<ets>litre</ets>. See <er>Liter</er>.]</ety> <def>A measure of capacity
or volume in the metric system; one tenth of a liter, equal to 6.1022
cubic inches, or 3.38 fluid ounces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

